A new online radio station will hit the airwaves on the  KZN South Coast from 1 March. The station, Life FM KZN, is an initiative of youths on the lower South Coast. At a meeting chaired in Gandhinagar on the KZN North Coast on 15 February, the presenters and management discussed the way forward. The roles the presenters will play at Life FM KZN was confirmed at the meeting which was chaired by the programme manager, Mlu Doncabe. He said the station’s DJ’s will play pop, Kwaito, RnB, Maskandi, rock, hip-hop, gospel and house music. The station will operate from Bhai Plaza in uMzinto. [mc4wp_form id=”44957″]